This wizard converts an Integration Services project from the package deployment model to the project deployment model by converting packages and configurations from SQL Server 2008, SQL Server 2008 R2 and SQL Server 2005 to {0} format. Because this wizard was started from BI Development Studio the original project (.dtproj) and package (.dtsx) files will be upgraded. It is recommended you create a backup of these files before proceeding.

This wizard will generate a project deployment file (.ispac) from a set of packages and configurations. The deployment file is a compiled project, consisting of packages and parameters. After conversion, the project can be deployed to an Integration Services catalog on an instance of SQL Server. The original package (.dtsx) files will not be modified. To convert the packages themselves to the {0}, launch this wizard from within BI Development Studio.
There are seven steps to completing this wizard:
1. Select the Integration Services packages that you want to convert.
4. Select configurations that you want to convert.
There are seven steps to completing this wizard:
1. Select the Integration Services packages that you want to convert.
2. Select the destination of the new project deployment file.
4. Select configurations that you want to convert.
